Halve @ciabatta bread{2}; toast in a #toaster until golden.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce. Slice @tomato{1} into ¼-inch rounds. Tear or slice @prosciutto{2%oz} crosswise into bite-size pieces.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss @arugula{2%oz} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Spread @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} onto cut sides of bottom ciabatta halves. Spread @fig jam{1} onto cut sides of top ciabatta halves; sprinkle with as many @chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like. Layer bottom ciabatta halves with as much dressed arugula as you like. Top with prosciutto, @gouda cheese{2%slices}, and tomato. Close sandwiches.

Halve sandwiches on a diagonal; divide between #plates{} and serve with any remaining arugula on the side.